90's film was the best over all. The turtles were the main focus, there was 
an awesome build up to the reveal of the shredder to the turtles in the 
end, while he's mostly lurking around. The turtles weren't ninja hulks 
fighting a transformer. Their size rendered a ninja foot clan obsolete in 
this one. If you're not shooting at them with guns, then there is no hope 
of physically over powering them. Of course, Banes mercenaries, err, I mean 
the foot clan can't even hit a soft spot on the turtles with all that fire 
power anyway. The 2nd film will have to have Beebop and Rocksteady in it 
just so there is someone other than the shredder to fight them. Lets not 
forget about the sewer slip-n-slide retardation. How does a shot of 
adrenaline magically replace the fact that their blood has been drained? 
The 11? hours of unrealistic Hashi torture by Splinter. The action, as she 
said, was terrible in the new one. A lot of swatting bad guys aside because 
they're turtle hulks and a lack luster fight with IronShredder and his 
flying blades. The 90's had numerous large fights with an actual ninja foot 
clan that displayed actual martial arts. The turtles acted more like ninjas 
and lurked around at night time in the dark. They didn't go flipping across 
the edge of roof tops in broad day light for everyone to see, advertising 
there are giant turtle humanoids in existence. Speaking of flipping, why 
the hell did giant 6-7 foot turtle hulks have to flip every 2 seconds? 
 T.U.R.T.L.E. Power was a much better end credits song than Shell shocked. 
The list of fails for the new movie is large and plentiful and them being 
Aprils pets/daddy's lab experiments for a cure (why the hell would they use 
turtles and not lab mice like everyone else?) was lame. The turtle van was 
actually cool, but seemed too small given their size. Argh, it's 90's 
turtle movie or bust at this point. It's just too bad they dumbed down the 
2nd movie (secrets of the ooze) because the first was too dark...﻿

characters.

Judith Hoag as April O'Neil.  She acts like a real person...and not like
